    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Assistant Driller evacuated to shore by boat on July 5, 2023 at 1:00 am",
      "BSEE investigation conducted on July 10 and July 12, 2023",
      "Second back-up line added to wrench after investigation",
      "Video footage of incident reviewed by investigators"
    ],
    "summary": "On July 3, 2023, a spinning wrench rotated approximately 30 inches and struck the Assistant Driller in the hard hat and head while he was standing at the wrench controls during drilling operations on the Enterprise 264 rig. The wrench was improperly installed with only one back-up line instead of the two required by the manufacturer's user manual, allowing excessive rotational movement. The AD was diagnosed with a concussion and evacuated to shore two days after the incident. Investigation revealed the user manual was not readily available to rig personnel, and rig personnel were trained on the job without written procedures.",
    "recommendations": [],
